cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SY

The paper proposes a solution for global optimization using generative neural networks to model point search distributions. This approach falls under the category of machine learning and optimization, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a machine learning approach using generative neural networks to model search distributions. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper uses evolutionary search as inspiration for the proposed solution, and the use of neural networks to model search distributions falls under the category of neural computing. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): Global optimization is a subfield of artificial intelligence, and the paper proposes an AI-based solution using neural networks. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes an algorithmic solution for global optimization, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms. 

cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a solution for optimization, which is a key component of control systems.
